    <item>
      <title>Using VMware.Sdk.Vcf.SddcManager: Commands for SDDC Manager in PowerCLI</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/post/vcf-90/vcf-90-powercli-sddcm-cmdlets/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 17 Jul 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <author>gblake@jadenetworks.co.uk (Gary Blake)</author>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/post/vcf-90/vcf-90-powercli-sddcm-cmdlets/</guid>
      <description>
        
          
            <p>VCF PowerCLI 9.0 now includes a module called <code>VMware.Sdk.Vcf.SddcManager</code>, this modules contains auto-generated cmdlets to support SDDC Manager Public APIs. Use can use this post as a quick reference guide.</p>
<h3 id="connecting-to-a-sddc-manager-instance-with-local-credentials">Connecting to a SDDC Manager Instance with Local Credentials</h3>
<ol>
<li>
<p>Start a PowerShell session.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Connect to a SDDC Manager instance using local credentials by running the following command:</p>
</li>
</ol>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell"><span class="line"><span class="ln">1</span><span class="cl"><span class="nb">Connect-VcfSddcManagerServer</span> <span class="n">-Server</span> <span class="nb">sfo-vcf01</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="py">sfo</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="py">rainpole</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="py">io</span> <span class="n">-User</span> <span class="n">administrator</span><span class="nv">@vsphere</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="py">local</span> <span class="n">-Password</span> <span class="n">VMw</span><span class="nv">@re1</span><span class="p">!</span><span class="n">VMw</span><span class="nv">@re1</span><span class="p">!</span>
</span></span></code></pre></div><ol start="3">
<li>Once connected the following information is stored in <code>$defaultSddcManagerConnections</code>.</li>
</ol>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span class="line"><span class="ln"> 1</span><span class="cl">ServiceUri     : https://sfo-vcf01.sfo.rainpole.io/
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="ln"> 2</span><span class="cl">SessionSecret  : &lt;sessionSecret&gt;
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="ln"> 3</span><span class="cl">User           : administrator@vsphere.local
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="ln"> 4</span><span class="cl">IsConnected    : True
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="ln"> 5</span><span class="cl">Id             : /VcfSddcManagerServer<span class="o">=</span>administrator@vsphere.local@sfo-vcf01.sfo.rainpole.io:443/
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="ln"> 6</span><span class="cl">Name           : sfo-vcf01.sfo.rainpole.io
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="ln"> 7</span><span class="cl">Uid            : /VcfSddcManagerServer<span class="o">=</span>administrator@vsphere.local@sfo-vcf01.sfo.rainpole.io:443/
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="ln"> 8</span><span class="cl">ProductVersion : 9.0.0.0.24703748
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="ln"> 9</span><span class="cl">ServerUri      : https://sfo-vcf01.sfo.rainpole.io/
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="ln">10</span><span class="cl">UUID           : /VcfSddcManagerServer<span class="o">=</span>administrator@vsphere.local@sfo-vcf01.sfo.rainpole.io:443/
</span></span><span class="line"><span class="ln">11</span><span class="cl">Port           : <span class="m">443</span>
</span></span></code></pre></div><ol start="4">
<li>Disconnect from a SDDC Manager instance by running the following command:</li>
</ol>
<div class="highlight"><pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"><code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell"><span class="line"><span class="ln">1</span><span class="cl"><span class="nb">Disconnect-VcfSddcManagerServer</span> <span class="n">-Server</span> <span class="nb">sfo-vcf01</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="py">sfo</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="py">rainpole</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="py">io</span>
</span></span></code></pre></div><h3 id="display-all-sddc-manager-get-command-details">Display All SDDC Manager GET Command Details</h3>
